text: King Fahd bin Abdul Aziz Al Saud, Custodian of the Two Holy Mosques, ( - August 1, 2005) was the King of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia. He was also the leader of the House of Saud and Prime Minister. One of his sons was Abdul Aziz bin Fahd. == Notes == ==References== Category:1920s births Category:2005 deaths Category:Deaths from pneumonia Category:Disease-related deaths in Saudi Arabia Category:Kings of Saudi Arabia Category:Prime Ministers of Saudi Arabia Category:21st-century kings of Saudi Arabia
